  "texts": [
    "In this paper, the influence of the K-order approximation of the local spectral filter on the model is studied, as shown in Figure 5B, the model performs stably in the classification task with the increase of the graph convolutional layer.",
    "When the graph convolutional layer is 8, the model performance begins to decrease as the increases of K. When the graph convolutional layer reaches 16, the model performance drops significantly, and at that time, the model performance drops the fastest.",
    "However, when the hierarchical convolution operation is performed, the model performance increases with the increase of the graph convolutional layer, and when the graph convolutional layer is 16, the model performance reaches the best.",
    "Therefore, D2GCN, restricts hierarchical convolution operations.",
